              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/18/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: DM1 management, weight loss update.
HPI: 55yo AA male with DM1 x 41 years on insulin pump. Started semaglutide 1mg Jan 2025 for weight/insulin resistance. Down 12 lbs (260-&gt;248). A1c improved 7.8-&gt;7.2. Reports 1 hypoglycemic episode Feb 2026 (BG 52, treated with glucose tabs). CGM shows TIR 72%.
Pump settings: Basal reduced 15% since starting semaglutide. ICR 1:8, CF 1:35.
PE: BMI 34.6 (was 36.3). Feet -- diminished monofilament bilateral, pedal pulses 1+. No ulcers.
Assessment:
# DM1 (E10.22): A1c 7.2 improving. Continue pump + semaglutide. Review CGM data -- adjust basal overnight.
# CKD 3b (N18.32): Cr 1.8, eGFR 42, UACR 180. Continue losartan. Nephrology co-manages.
# Neuropathy (E10.42): Pain controlled on pregabalin + duloxetine.
# Hyperlipidemia: LDL at goal. TG still 340. Fenofibrate adequate dose.
# Obesity: 12 lbs lost. Target another 20 lbs.
# Retinopathy: Annual ophthalmology visit due -- scheduled.
Plan: Continue all meds. CGM download next visit. Nephrology 3 months. Ophthalmology annual. A1c in 3 months.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>09/10/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Annual Wellness Visit</td><td>ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT -- G0439
55yo male with DM1, CKD.
Preventive:
- Colorectal: Cologuard 2024 negative. Next 2027.
- Depression: PHQ-9 = 10 (moderate). Continue duloxetine.
- Diabetic foot exam: Monofilament diminished. Podiatry referral.
- Diabetic eye exam: Retinopathy stable per ophthalmology 06/2025.
- Immunizations: Flu given. PCV20 given 2024.
- PSA: Discussed, patient declines (informed refusal documented).
Advance Directive: On file, updated.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
